## 🎯 NestJS Architectural Rules
- Follow the **default modular architecture** (modules, controllers, providers).
- Each feature = 1 module (e.g., AuthModule, UsersModule, EventsModule).
- Root `AppModule` imports all feature modules.
- Place shared utilities (guards, pipes, interceptors) in a CommonModule.
- Avoid “God modules”; keep modules cohesive and decoupled.

## Controllers & Services
- Controllers handle routing & validation only.
- Services contain business logic and access repositories.
- Use DTOs and `class-validator` for request/response validation.
- Use interfaces/abstracts for contracts.
- Throw HTTP exceptions properly (BadRequestException, etc.).
- Use dependency injection (`@Injectable()`).
- Avoid request-scoped providers unless necessary.

## Config & Bootstrapping
- Use `@nestjs/config` for environment configs.
- Keep secrets in env variables.
- Apply global pipes, filters, interceptors in `main.ts`.
- Use `app.enableShutdownHooks()` for graceful shutdown.
